Jamilu-IIiyasu Birnin-Magaji  has been appointed by Gov. Bello Matawalle of Zamfara as  Press Secretary. This was contained in a letter by the Secretary to the State Government (SSG), Alhaji Bala Bello, in Gusau on Sunday. The governor said that the appointment takes effect from Sept. 14. Birnin-Magaji was the former Secretary to Zamfara Council of the Nigeria Union of Journalists (NUJ). Until his appointment, the new Press Secretary was a news editor at the state owned Radio and Television Stations as well as MC at government house, Gusau. Responding to his appointment, Birnin-Magaji, promised to be more dedicated and hardworking in the discharge of his duties to the people of the state.